<tr>
<td bgcolor="#EEEEEE" colspan=2 class=news>
<table><tr><td valign=top><img src='images/icon_general.gif' alt='General News' border=0></td><td width="100%" valign=top><IMG SRC="http://www.buda.nildram.co.uk/flash.jpg" align=left> The <A HREF="http://www.flashpoint1985.com/download/patches_flag.html" class=colourise target=_new>Operation Flashpoint downloads page</A> has had an updated Flag pack put up on it.<br>What's been added?<br><span class=quote>Flags of Australia, England, Wales, Scotland and other national flags.</span><br>The link to it on their page is broken because of a typo, so use <A HREF="ftp://www.flashpoint1985.com/OFPAddOn_FlagPack_updated.zip" class=colourise>this link</A> for the correct download.<br><br>Marek Spanel has also just released word via the <A HREF="http://www.flashpoint1985.com/cgi-bin/ikonboard/topic.cgi?forum=19&topic=2" class=colourise target=_new>Operation Flashpoint Forum</A> about the next Flashpoint Version.<br>Here's the stuff:<br><span class=quote>Version 1.26 of Operation Flashpoint executable is coming out soon (ETA: Friday Oct 12) and it will be available as public beta. New version will introduce dramatically reworked and improved netcode and over 50 of other bug fixes and improvements. More information coming soon...</span><br><br>Initial source of both pieces of information was [ <A HREF="http://www.bluesnews.com/" class=colourise target=_new>Blue's News</A> ]</td></tr></table>
</td>
